s and awarded the contract worth more than  billion to walbridge thanks to the k car deal chrysler ceo lee iacocca viewed walbridge as not just a contractor but as a strategic partnerdetroit free pressredeveloping detroit remains long hard slogwhen we were selected to be the contractor for the chrysler technology center mr iacocca made a point of telling us that ‘you won the project fair and square but that put the icing on the cake there have been many such dramatic moments in the history of walbridge which formed in  as walbridge aldinger a partnership between building expert george walbridge and financial expert albert aldingernow simply walbridge the firm has built dozens of iconic structures in its hometown of detroit including the penobscot building book tower orchestra hall the detroit people mover one detroit center and compuware headquartersmost identified for its automotive work walbridge work included fords rouge plant in the late s and again in this century general motors wind tunnel at its warren tech center in the s and visteons headquarters campus in van buren township in  the company now employs about  workers and does more than  billion a year in revenuewalbridge survived the great depression doing work for maxwell motor car by doing maintenance on railroad lines and other work it could pick up once world war ii began walbridge turned to defense projects building vast munitions factories for the government in missouri and minnesota factories that produced billions of rounds of ammunition photo walbridgebut the companys greatest crisis came after the war when founders walbridge and aldinger died leaving an ownership conundrum for the pairs several other partners who owned pieces of the firm the firm survived the crisis because of a culture that valued service and continuityeach time somebody sold to the succeeding group they left a little on the table for the next guy rakolta said they didn’t extract every single last dollar in value that the company might have been worth they sold at a discount so there was protection for the next guy so in case the economy went down or they had a couple job losses they wouldn’t be stretched to the limitjust prior to the chrysler tech center contract the firm acquired its largest competitor at the time a company called darin and armstrong and added  employees to its own  that provided more expertise and personnel enabling the firm to go after bigger jobs and to take more risks you have to have a big appetite for risk to be in this business rakolta saidtoday the firm employs about  staffers and works throughout the us and in several other countries reported annual revenues top  billion the firm is headquartered in the one kennedy square building near campus martius in downtown detroitthe rakolta family has long been involved in the firm as principal owners and executives going back more than  years ceo rakolta started working at the firm as a youthful intern in the s his son john rakolta iii serves as chief financial officer today and is in line to be  the next ceo when his father retires a daughter lauren is president of a facilities management subsidiary other children hold ownership stakes in the firmbuy photo photo salwan georges detroit free pressthe companys motto is built for good a mantra that emphasizes service to customers the community and colleaguesweve had a great  years rakolta said there’s very few companies on a national scale that have been able to survive that long our goal today is to set this company up to have another  years so that the guy sitting in my chair in  will most likely be saying exactly the same things that i’m saying today culture is what makes all the differencecontact john gallagher  gallagherfreepresscom or on twitter jgallagherfreep  connecttweet  linkedin  commentemailmoreread or share this story httponfreepcomrtyxd john rakolta jr chairman and ceo  walbridge john rakolta jr chairman and ceo  walbridge asset ®  leadership  john rakolta jr john rakolta jr john is the seventh individual to lead walbridge in its year history as a boy his grandfather drove john to the company’s equipment and maintenance yard to mow the lawn john’s father john rakolta sr joined walbridge in  as a timekeeper and later served as president ceo chairman and chairman emeritus from  –  john jr received a bachelor of science degree in civil engineering from marquette university in  and later completed the smaller company management program at harvard business school  he joined the company in  as an estimator and held positions of increasing responsibility  he became president in  and succeeded his father as chairman and ceo in  during his tenure walbridge has grown from a regional constructor with annual sales of  million in the mids to a global entity registering sales of more than  billion in  walbridge is an acknowledged industry leader in the areas of safety quality and lean construction john has been a leader in both business and the community especially in the area of race relations and corporate citizenship he has been recognized with these honors awards dr gerald k smith humanitarian award black family development inc executive leadership award marketing and sales executives of detroit distinguished warrior award urban league of detroit and southeastern michigan john rakolta jr leadership in race relations award inaugural recipient new detroit rackham award engineering society of detroit master entrepreneur of the year award michigan and northwest ohio ernst  young woodrow wilson award for corporate citizenship woodrow wilson international center for scholars of the smithsonian institution a thirdgeneration romanianamerican john has served as romania’s honorary consul general to the united states in detroit since  in  he received the achievement in business and social involvement award from alianta a nonpartisan alliance of american and romanian organizations and professionals working to strengthen the cultural economic and security ties between the two countries john jr and his wife terry have four children eileen lauren paige and john iii our leadership team  walbridge our leadership team  walbridge asset ®  about  leadership leadership walbridge has been led during the past century by seven individuals each had a desire to succeed and exhibited strengths that propelled them to the top of the organization things like toughness tolerance for risk resilience and stepping up when the time came they also reminded generations of walbridge employees not to lose sight of key attributes established by our founders george walbridge and albert aldinger these are honesty integrity credibility trust and a passion for building learn more about the current members of our board of directors john rakolta jrchairman and ceo member board of directors john is the seventh individual to lead walbridge in its year history as a boy his grandfather drove john to read bio mike haller pepresident walbridge group member board of directors mike haller joined walbridge in  as a coop intern while pursuing a bachelor’s degree in civil engineering from the read bio john rakolta iiievp and cao member board of directors john rakolta iii joined the company in  and is well rounded in the business of construction with experience in read bio randy abdallahevp  get work member board of directors randy abdallah’s key responsibility is simply stated – get work he’s in charge of securing approximately  billion in sales read bio tom dyzeevp and chief risk officer member board of directors a certain level of risk is inherent in any construction project minimizing the level of risk is tom dyze’s job read bio terry merrittsenior vice president member board of directors terry is both a positive influence and role model at walbridge and an acknowledged leader among women throughout the great read bio news on john rakolta jr news home advertising board and executive moves energy health care hedge funds m  a private equity techn