d established in  assists and advises the governor regarding compliance with the us department of labor workforce investment act and overall talent development in the state prior to joining walbridge in  he worked for the athena group a real estate development and investment fund with offices in new york los angeles and washington dc john is the thirdgeneration member of the rakolta family to work for walbridge his father john rakolta jr is chairman and chief executive officer of the company and he succeeded his father john rakolta sr in those roles in  in  walbridge wwwwalbridgecom revenue exceeded  billion and in  the company was ranked the thlargest contractor in the united states by engineering newsrecord including ranking no  in domestic automotive manufacturing construction and no  in the same category internationally the company operates  offices in north america south america and the middle east john received a bachelor’s degree in building construction management from purdue university and a master’s degree in real estate finance and investment from new york university in january  john completed the program for leadership development at the harvard business school   coaa  construction owners association of america all rights reserved terms  conditions  privacy policy   antitrust policy  austell powder springs rd suite  austell ga   toll free    local    fax   follow us on twitter  tweets by coaahq follow us on facebook connect with us on linkedin connect with us on linkedin join our mailing list about coaa mission education leadership coaa project leadership award albert e phillips scholarship press room contact us volunteer central membership join coaa whatwho is an owner membersonly content chapters corporate sponsors conference call for presentations owner training institute owner training courses inhouse training upcoming webinars webinars  on demand lorman education workforce development initiative  coaa takes a stand collaboration chapters coaa ecatal